      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Need improvement\" is more direct and often suggests immediate, noticeable deficiencies requiring correction. Conversely, \"developmental opportunities\" is softer and frames the conversation around future growth and potential. While both point to areas needing work, the latter is less confrontational and focuses on skill-building rather than current failings. Choose based on whether you want to signal an urgent issue or guide ongoing growth.",
      "source": "target",
